The Musical Copyright Society Nigeria Ltd/Gte (MCSN) has elected new members of the General Council (board) to pilot the affairs of the Society for the next three years. Top Nigerian music stars and impresarios including Orits Williki, Tee Mac, and Kenny Keke Ogungbe were among the newly elected board members. The elections took place at its Annual General Meeting held in Lagos on Wednesday, June 29, 2022.   Depression notifies me when to switch my style – Rema     I’m inspired by Burna Boy’s tenancity – Blaqbonez     Yul Edochie calls out Ahmed Musa over post   Others elected to the board include Sunny Neji, Asha Fapohunda, Mathew Ohio, Victor Okhai, Segun Alile, Mojisola Fayemi, Mike Pam Mbala, and Kola Olulana. In a well-attended meeting, the Chairman’s report of events and developments as of December 31, 2021, the directors’ report for the year ended December 31, 2021, and the financial report for the year ended December 31, 2021, showed a great leap when compared with the previous year. In his address to the meeting, the President of the Society, King Sunny Ade called on the members of the Society to among other issues take a keen interest in the 2023 elections and ensure that they obtain their permanent voters’ cards to vote candidates of their choice.